{"parse":{"title":"fowl","pageid":53346,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{root|en|ine-pro|*plewk-}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|foul}}, {{m|enm|foghel}}, {{m|enm|fowel}}, {{m|enm|fowele}}, from {{inh|en|ang|fugol|t=bird}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*fugl}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*fuglaz}}, dissimilated variant of {{m|gem-pro|*fluglaz}} (compare {{cog|ang|flugol}} ‘fleeing’, Mercian ''fluglas heofun'' ‘birds of the air’),<ref>{{R:en:ODEE|fowl|374|1}}</ref> from {{m|gem-pro|*fleuganą|t= to [[fly]]}}. Cognate with {{cog|fy|fûgel}}, {{cog|nds|Vagel}}, {{cog|nl|vogel}}, {{cog|de|Vogel}}, {{cog|sv|fågel}}, {{cog|da,is,nb,nn|fugl}}. {{doublet|en|voël}}. More at [[fly]].\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{enPR|foul}}, {{IPA|en|/faʊl/}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-fowl.ogg|a=US}}\n** {{rhymes|en|aʊl|s=1}}\n* {{enPR|fou'''<nowiki/>''''əl}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈfaʊ.əl/}}\n** {{rhymes|en|aʊəl|s=2}}\n* {{homophones|en|foul}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{wp}}\n{{en-noun|*|s}}\n\n# {{lb|en|archaic}} Any [[bird]].\n#* {{RQ:Mlry MrtDrthr|15.19|2|XIII|xix|passage=And now I take vpon me the aduentures of holy thynges / & now I see and vnderstande that myn old synne hyndereth me and shameth me / so that I had no power to stere nor speke whan the holy blood appiered afore me / So thus he sorowed til hit was day / & herd the '''fowles''' synge / thenne somwhat he was comforted|t=And now I take upon myself the adventures of holy things / And now I see and understand that my old sin hinders me and shames me / so that I had no power to steer nor speak when the holy blood appeared afore me / So thus he sorrowed till it was day / and heard the '''fowls''' sing / then somewhat he was comforted}}\n# A bird hunted or kept for food, grouped into [[landfowl]] (order {{taxfmt|Galliformes|order}}), also called [[gamefowl]], and [[waterfowl]] (order {{taxfmt|Anseriformes|order}}: [[duck]]s, [[goose|geese]], [[swan]]s, etc.), which together form the [[clade]] {{taxfmt|Galloanserae|clade}}.\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|{{vern|fowl bluegrass}}, {{vern|fowl grass}}, {{vern|fowl meadow grass}} ({{taxlink|Poa palustris|species}})\n|antifowl|frizzle fowl\n|Cochin fowl\n|Dorking fowl\n|fowlery\n|fowl-house\n|fowlhouse\n|fowlish\n|fowlkind\n|fowl-like\n|fowllike\n|fowl-lore\n|fowl paralysis\n|fowl pest\n|fowlpox\n|fowl-run\n|fowlyard\n|gamefowl\n|game fowl\n|guinea fowl\n|guinea-fowl\n|helmeted guinea fowl\n|[[junglefowl]], [[jungle fowl]] ({{taxfmt|Gallus|genus}} spp.)\n|landfowl\n|make fish of one and fowl of another\n|mallee fowl\n|moorfowl\n|neither fish, flesh, nor fowl\n|neither fish nor fowl\n|peafowl\n|Philippine fowl disease\n|rockfowl\n|scrubfowl\n|seafowl\n|Spanish fowl\n|spurfowl\n|waterfowl\n|wildfowl\n|wormfowl\n|yardfowl\n}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|kri|fɔl}}\n* {{desc|srn|fowru}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-see|bird}}\n\n{{trans-top|bird of the order Galliformes}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|[[stuk]] [[pluimvee]]|n}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kanalintu}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|volaille|f}}\n* German: {{t|de|Stück Federvieh|n}}, {{t+|de|Geflügel|n}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|πουλερικό|n}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|baromfi}}, {{t+|hu|szárnyas}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|ayam}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|pollame|m}}\n* Javanese: {{t+|jv|pitik}}\n*: Old Javanese: {{t|kaw|pitik}}\n* Kodava: {{t|kfa|ಕೋಳಿ|tr=kōḷi}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|mājputns|m}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t|lt|naminis paukštis|m}}\n* Neapolitan: {{t|nap|pollo|m}}\n* Norwegian: {{t|nb|fjærfe|n}}\n* Occitan: {{t+|oc|polalha|f}}, {{t+|oc|volalha|f}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|ماکیان|tr=mâkiyân}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|drób|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|galiforme|m}}\n* Russian: {{t|ru|дома́шняя пти́ца|f}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|pjerina|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|ave|f}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|kümes hayvanı}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|طاوق|tr=tavuk}}, {{t|ota|مرغ|tr=mürg}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|gok}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|birds which are hunted or kept for food}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|gevogelte|n}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|riistalintu}} {{qualifier|hunted}}; {{t+|fi|siipikarja}} {{qualifier|kept}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|volaille|f}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Geflügel|n}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|πουλερικό|n}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|szárnyas}}, {{t|hu|víziszárnyas}}\n* Icelandic: {{t|is|fiðurfé|n}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|éanlaith|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|volatile|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|живина|f}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|ptactwo|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|[[ave]] [[de]] [[criação]]/[[corte]]|f}}\n* Russian: {{t|ru|перна́тая дичь|f}} {{qualifier|hunted}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|hydina|f-p}} {{qualifier|kept}}, {{t|sk|hyd|m-p}} {{qualifier|kept}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|pjerina|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|ave|f}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|kümes hayvanı}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|طاوق|tr=tavuk}}, {{t|ota|مرغ|tr=mürg}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Welsh: {{t-check|cy|dofedn}}, {{t-check|cy|ffowlyn}}, {{t-check|cy|ffowl}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|verb}} To [[hunt]] fowl.\n#: {{ux|en|We took our guns and went '''fowling'''.}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|en|fowler}}\n* {{l|en|fowling}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|to hunt fowl}}\n* Middle English: {{t|enm|foulen}}\n* Polish: {{t|pl|[[polować]] [[na]] [[drób]]|impf}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|adara}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====References====\n<references/>\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Adjective====\n{{en-adj|er}}\n\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} [[foul]]\n#* ''Paradise Lost, John Milton''\n#*: Say first, for Heav'n hides nothing from thy view / Nor the deep Tract of Hell, say first what cause / Mov'd our Grand Parents in that happy State / Favour'd of Heav'n so highly, to fall off / From their Creator, and transgress his Will / For one restraint, Lords of the World besides? / Who first seduc'd them to that '''fowl''' revolt?\n\n====References====\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n* {{R:Century 1911}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=flow|Wolf|flow|wolf}}\n\n{{C|en|Fowls}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|foul|id=bird|t=bird}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Adjective====\n{{head|enm|adjective|altform=1}} \n\n# {{lb|enm|late}} {{alt form|enm|foul|id=foul|t=foul}}"}}